{"id":"261066019_Sample-Optimal_Fourier_Sampling_in_Any_Constant_Dimension_--_Part_I","abstract":"We give an algorithm for $\\ell_2/\\ell_2$ sparse recovery from Fourier\nmeasurements using $O(k\\log N)$ samples, matching the lower bound of\n\\cite{DIPW} for non-adaptive algorithms up to constant factors for any $k\\leq\nN^{1-\\delta}$. The algorithm runs in $\\tilde O(N)$ time. Our algorithm extends\nto higher dimensions, leading to sample complexity of $O_d(k\\log N)$, which is\noptimal up to constant factors for any $d=O(1)$. These are the first sample\noptimal algorithms for these problems.\nA preliminary experimental evaluation indicates that our algorithm has\nempirical sampling complexity comparable to that of other recovery methods\nknown in the literature, while providing strong provable guarantees on the\nrecovery quality.","authors":["Piotr Indyk","Michael Kapralov"],"meta":["March 2014","DOI:10.1109/FOCS.2014.61","SourcearXiv"],"references":["261038447_A_100MHz-2GHz_125x_sub-Nyquist_rate_receiver_in_90nm_CMOS","230570680_Universality_in_Polytope_Phase_Transitions_and_Message_PassingAlgorithms","230569090_Adaptive_sub-linear_Fourier_algorithms","228325302_Restricted_Isometry_of_Fourier_Matrices_and_List_Decodability_of_RandomLinear_Codes","226594106_Combinatorial_Sublinear-Time_Fourier_Algorithms","221591507_Tight_RMR_Lower_Bounds_for_Mutual_Exclusion_and_Other_Problems","221499125_Mutual_Exclusion_with_Olog2_Log_n_Amortized_Work","221497317_Deterministic_Sparse_Fourier_Approximation_Via_Approximating_Arithmetic_Progressions","221344293_Adaptive_Randomized_Mutual_Exclusion_in_Sub-Logarithmic_Expected_Time","221233796_Sub-logarithmic_Test-and-Set_against_a_Weak_Adversary","220692283_Parallel_Computer_Architecture_A_Hardware-Software_Approach","220567027_Randomized_mutual_exclusion_with_sub-logarithmic_RMR-complexity","312488186_Algorithms_for_scalable_synchronization_on_shared-memory_multiprocessors","305263121_Solution_of_a_Problem_in_Concurrent_Programmi